    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit is mechanically superlative, showcasing a linear power delivery via six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system that has been fully bulletproofed. The Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile engagement, sending torque to a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance is complete: the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced with plates, and the rod bearings have been replaced with VAC Motorsports coated shells. The chassis remains taut with zero bushing play, and the factory-correct dampers maintain original rebound and compression specs. Finished in a mirror-like Carbon Black Metallic with zero cowl or undercarriage oxidation, this specimen represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated M-division engineering.",
